Class Species

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectfx.species.Species
All Implemented Interfaces:
Movable, Reproducible, Sleepable
Direct Known Subclasses:
Carnivore, Herbivore, Omnivore
public abstract class Species extends Object implements Movable, Reproducible, Sleepable
The Species class represents a species in the ecosystem. This is an abstract class that implements the interfaces for Movable, Reproducible, and Sleepable. Each species has a name, energy level, position in the environment, and behaviors related to movement, reproduction, energy consumption, and sleeping. Specific species classes (e.g., Rabbit, Shark) extend this class and implement their own versions of methods like eat, move, and reproduce.

      public Species(String name, int energy, Positionn positionn, Environment environment, int vitesse, javafx.scene.image.ImageView imageView)
      Constructs a new Species with the specified attributes. This constructor initializes the name, energy, position, environment, and movement speed of the species. The species is initially set to be awake (sleeping = false).
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the species.
      energy - The initial energy of the species.
      positionn - The position of the species in the environment.
      environment - The environment the species belongs to.
      vitesse - The movement speed of the species.
      imageView - The image representation of the species.
